##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PCCmacros.pl",
  "answerHints.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("LimitedNumeric");
$a=random(2,50,1)*-1;
$b=random(2,500,3);
$c=random(2,10,1);

$ans = Compute("$a");

##############################################
TEXT(beginproblem());
BEGIN_PGML
Use the properties of exponents to simplify the expression.
   
    [`
       [$a]\cdot\left(-[$b]^{[$c]}\right)^0=
    `] [______]

END_PGML

ANS($ans -> cmp() ->
  withPostFilter(AnswerHints(
    [Compute("0")] =>
    "The answer is not 0; have a look at the zero-exponent rule and try again.")));


BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
The zero-exponent rule says that [`a^0=1`] where [`a`] is any real number except [`0`]; note that we don't have 
to evaluate [`-[$b]^{[$c]}`] since the whole quantity is raised to the power [`0`]

    [`
         \begin{aligned}
       [$a]\cdot\left(-[$b]^{[$c]}\right)^0&=[$a]\cdot 1\\
                     & = [$a]
         \end{aligned}
    `]

END_PGML_SOLUTION
